            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>coated chicken</strong> to one side of a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 20 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>crispy onion chicken</strong></p><p>While the chicken is cooking, dissolve your <strong>soy sauce</strong> and <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 200ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [260ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>with your<strong> onion marmalade </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> – this is your <strong>gravy stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1701095154568-x200.jpg",
